name: Ground floor apartment near Vondelpark with garden
description: Smart 95m2 ground floor apartment close to Vondelpark and city centre. Completely renovated and redecorated in 2017 with a nice city garden to have dinner or relax in. neighborhood_overview:
Enjoy your breakfast or lunch at Vlaams Broodhuys on the corner or at Lavinia or Anne&Max around the other corner! Or take away and eat them on our bench in front of the house and see the world go by. In the evening the Main Street (Amstelveenseweg) has many excellent restaurants to offer like Dragon I or Blauw . Maybe you’ll prefer the high quality Ron gastrobar or queuing up with the locals for a Indonesian take away. If you want to eat at home a supermarket, fish shop, butcher and other shops are within 50 meters.
The Vondelpark is 200 m away. Locals lounge, play and walk in it. You could walk to the museums, the smart area round Cornelis Schuytstraat or city centre, but you can also catch tram 2 which has a stops next to these locations and ends at the central train station.

name: Cozy home & rooftop near center (6 adults& 2 kids)
description: Cozy apartment on the top floor of a typical late 1800s building in Amsterdam's lively neighborhood De Pijp, overlooking the beautiful Sarphatipark. Quiet, light, and very private for this area's standards because of its location, with a rooftop terrace. Beware of the STEEP stairs, though - my place is very comfy once inside, but you need to be rather fit and brave to haul your luggage upstairs. Also, note that Dutch houses were not built for hot weather and typically have no A/C.
neighborhood_overview: De Pijp is one of Amsterdam's hippest neighborhoods, with the highest density of stops, bars, and restaurants per square meter, plus the largest permanent street market right around the corner. You really don't have to leave the neighborhood; I seldom do. However, if you must visit Amsterdam's touristy highlights, they are all within reach. You can walk, bike or use public transport to any of them within 20 minutes.
host_about: Born and raised in Amsterdam, I set out to explore the world at a young age. Over the past four decades I have traveled to over thirty countries, and have lived in three of those. Currently, I am back at my habitat Amsterdam, where I am working as a self-employed co-creator (thecocreatorscom) and raising my three sons (13, 9, and 3 years old). Since 2021 I am also the co-ordinator of Wijkcentrum De Pijp, helping people improve our hood.

name: Ruime boven woning met dakterras en uitzicht
description: Forget your worries in this spacious and serene space.
neighborhood_overview:
De Baarsjes is a lively and diverse area in the west of Amsterdam, the Netherlands. It is a popular residential area for young professionals, families and students due to its central location and excellent public transport connections.

The neighborhood has a rich history, with many buildings dating back to the beginning of the 20th century. The Baarsjes was once a popular neighborhood, but in recent years it has undergone a considerable upgrade, with many trendy bars, restaurants and boutiques.

One of the highlights of De Baarsjes is the Rembrandtpark, a large public park that offers a peaceful escape from the hustle and bustle of the city. The park has hiking and biking trails, playgrounds, and a lake, making it a popular spot for families and lovers of outdoor living.

De Baarsjes also has a vibrant food culture, with many international restaurants offering a wide range of dishes. Whether you're hungry for sushi, Italian or Dutch cuisine, you can find
host_about:
Ik woon inmmidels 5 jaar, samen met mijn dochter die om de week bij mij is, in dit 100m2 appartement van twee verdiepingen. 
Het appartement ligt centraal met restaurants, café's, winkels en openbaar vervoer op loopafstand.

description: This stylish, spacious and bright two-floor apartment is located in the de Pijp neighbourhood in central Amsterdam, one of the city's trendiest areas. The house is a typical two-storied Amsterdam home. On the main floor, you will find a bright living room with an open kitchen that is fully equipped for cooking. The flat has a balcony that overlooks a green courtyard, perfect for sunny breakfasts. The spacious bedroom is located on the second floor together with a modern shower with a bath.
neighborhood_overview:
De Pijp neighbourhood is one of Amsterdam’st most fashionable areas that is famous for its boutique stores, vintage shops as well as countless quality restaurants and cosy cafes.

The flat is a one-minute walk from Amsterdam's largest street market, the colourful Albert Cuypmarkt and a three-minute stroll from the tranquil Saphatipark.

Though de Pijp is a bustling area, the flat is located on a calm side street. If you are looking for a neighbourhood that is far away from the city’s seedy “tourist zones,” de Pijp is your place to be.

Amsterdam’s Museum Quarter ( Rijksmuseum, Van Gogh Museum, Stedelijk Museum) is only a 15-minute walk away. The flat is It is also easily reachable from Schiphol Airport by taxi (20 minutes) or with public transport from Central Station.

We will leave you a list of our favourite go-to cafes and restaurants.

The property is part of a unique residential area of 40 self-designed sustainable houseboats. The residential park is divided into 3 floors. On the upper floor (split level) a TV and a rooftop terrace. At the first floor, kitchen and living. Downstairs bedroom for 2 adults and a children's room for 2. Bathroom with bathtub and generous shower.
neighborhood_overview: The home is part of a sustainable eco district "Schoonschip Amsterdam" It is a fine child-friendly residential area with 40 unique self-designed living parks. There is a lot of swimming, tuping and canoeing. Within 10 minutes by bike, you are in the heart of Amsterdam Centrum. The creative heart of NDSM is a 10-minute walk away, with cozy cafes and restaurants.

neighborhood_overview:
Explore the Charming Heart of Amsterdam: The Canals and Culture of Central Amsterdam
Central Amsterdam is a picturesque area known for its historic architecture, iconic canals, and vibrant cultural scene. This neighborhood, nestled among Amsterdam's famous canals and close to key attractions, offers an ideal blend of tranquility and urban excitement. It's an area that effortlessly combines the charm of old Amsterdam with the conveniences of modern city life, making it one of the best places to stay for both short and extended visits.

Iconic Canals and Historic Architecture
One of the defining features of this neighborhood is its stunning network of canals, which are part of the UNESCO World Heritage-listed Canal Ring. These waterways not only offer scenic beauty but also a unique way to explore the city, whether by boat, bike, or on foot. The northern part of Amsterdam is currently the most upcoming, dynamic and exciting part of the city. New cafés and restaurants, galleries, art projects, innovative architecture, and the likes. The EYE film theater and cafe/restaurant is one of the most impressive places and view points in the city, the new THT cultural center and restaurant, etc. are all around the corner.

We look forward to meeting you!

name: Stylish & Quiet Apartment near Vondelpark
description:
Bright fully equipped apartment of 57m2 located on the 1st floor, in a peaceful area and close to the center of Amsterdam. A private terrace of 12m2 overlooks a quiet, tree-lined courtyard.

The accommodation located 1 km from two parks (Vondelpark and Rembrandtpark) and close to all shops is ideal for couples, with or without children.

We have a baby room which can be used.
neighborhood_overview:
This apartment is located in the "Hoofddorpplein" neighbourhood, which is located in the district "Amsterdam-Zuid".

The neighborhood was built in the twenties. The characteristic architectural style can be found everywhere in the streetscape, such as the eccentric housing porticoes and the pointed corner towers.

Two beautiful parks, Vondelpark and Rembrandtpark, are just around the corner: 5 minutes by bike or 15 minutes walk.
In the summer, you can relax (and even swim!) at the Stadiongracht or in Park Schinkeleilanden.

This quiet neighborhood is popular with families, students and couples. It is very conveniently located near the station Amsterdam-Zuid where all train, metro, and tram connections are available. Also the neighborhood is surrounded by the A10 so you will be on the highways in no time. Schiphol Airport is only at 10 minutes from the apartment by car.
host_about:
Bonjour ! 

Française habitant depuis 2017 à Amsterdam, je travaille ici en tant qu'Architecte d'Intérieur. Je suis tombée amoureuse de cette ville dès l'instant où je suis arrivée.. Se déplacer en vélo tous les jours, la présence de nombreux parcs et une atmosphère chaleureuse et bienveillante - été comme hiver (oui, même sous la pluie !) m'ont vite convaincu de m'installer définitivement ici !

J'espère que vous aimerez autant que moi cette jolie capitale au caractère si atypique.. Bon séjour à Amsterdam !

neighborhood_overview: Oud West is close to the city-centre and close to both Vondelpark and Rembrandtpark. Kinkerstraat is a multicultural area with a large shopping street filled with bars, restaurants, clothes etc. It’s criss-crossed with commercial streets, including Overtoom which has become a major interiors boulevard. Two of the city’s more interesting alternative cultural complexes, OT301 and Lab111, which both mix music, film and art, are located here. But for a real taste for the relaxed diversity of this neighbourhood, visit the sprawling terrace of Du Cap to truly witness all walks of life. And again: the whole city is pretty much nearby.

name: Minimal apartment amsterdam oost
description:
A beautiful apartment on the bustling Javastraat in Amsterdam East. The javastraat is known for its cozy restaurants, bars and boutiques. The apartment is stylishly and minimalistically furnished and features a spacious sunny living room with French south-facing balcony. The bedroom is located at the quiet rear of the apartment.

neighborhood_overview:
The Javastraat is located in the heart of Amsterdam. It is a very special street. After all, an entire book was written about Javastraat and a person spent 365 days without leaving it, making vlogs about the street everyday. I remember the first day I stepped foot there. I was fascinated by Javastraat’s colours, its noise, and its crowd, how it glistened with excitement that awaited at every corner. The street moved like a pulsating wave towards me and I was ready to absorb it all at once. Day after day, I would explore the street better, which gave me the strength to venture further into the city — but still, whenever I return to Javastraat I feel like returning home.

Soon, I would discover more and more about Javastraat’s treasures. I was delighted by the falafels of Tarbush and Tigris Eufrat; I enjoyed the cosiness of De Jonge Admiraal and the youthful friendliness of Bar Basquiat; I was mesmerised by the richness of local shops and the wondrous ingredients they offered

host_about:

neighborhood_overview:
IJburg is a district in Amsterdam, the tram rides every 2-5 minutes, the stop is on the corner and will bring you to Central Station in 15 minutes.
IJburg is a modern and new district in Amsterdam, with lovely and modern architecture. Water, free views, wind, nature, but also the benefits of living in the city. It's a quiet, spacious and childfriendly neighbourhood, with lots of water and parks. During summertime you can swim or sail a boat, we have an inflatable SUP, during winter time you can ice skate. host_about:
Ik woon sinds mijn studententijd in Amsterdam, en inmiddels werk ik er als verloskundige. Het is een wereldse stad, maar toch met een dorps gevoel. IJburg is een nieuwe wijk bij Amsterdam, met prachtige architectuur. Je hebt hier de voordelen van buitenaf wonen; water, vrij uitzicht, wind, natuur, maar ook de voordelen van de grote stad heel erg dichtbij. 
Ik en mijn 3 kinderen zijn niet altijd thuis, en graag maak ik het voor anderen mogelijk om mijn huis te huren en zo Amsterdam en IJburg te leren kennen. Perfect geschikt voor gezinnen door het aantal slaapplekken en de rustige ligging, maar ook zeer geschikt voor mensen zonder kinderen, die Amsterdam en omgeving willen verkennen.
Mede door mijn werk als verloskundige heb ik de stad tot in de puntjes leren kennen en deze kennis deel ik graag met anderen.

name: Oud-West/Jordaan with canal view
description: A modern renovated 55m2 2-room apartment with a large rooftop terrace, including canal view. Living room with open kitchen, 1 bedroom and a bright bathroom! This lovely apartment is perfectly located within walking distance to the famous Jordaan and the 9 streets. Suitable for up to 2 persons
neighborhood_overview:
You are ideally situated in Amsterdam Oud West (Old West), in the city center of Amsterdam, making it very easy for you to explore the city by foot. It is a friendly district, which has coffee shops, trendy bars/ restaurants and cozy lunchrooms on every corner.
You will find yourself right in the middle of many well worth visiting sites, such as the Vondelpark, Leidseplein, Rijks museum, Stedelijk museum and the Van Gogh museum. Here you can also find the P.C. - Hoofdstraat, where all the luxurious brands such as Hugo Boss, Ralph Lauren and Mulberry are located. And if you love shopping, you can’t miss the Jordaan, with the '9 straatjes'. In this authentic neighbourhood you will find lots of lovely small boutiques, bars and restaurants. But also the famous “Anne Frank” museum is situated here.
Whether you love the arts, shopping or spending your time exploring Dutch pubs/ restaurants and the nightlife, this part of the city offers you the possibility to enjoy most of these
host_about:
Dear guests,

After living in Amsterdam for 22 years and having become a consultant Oral and Maxillofacial Surgery, my wife Patty and I, together with our 3 young children, moved to a place closer to the sea and nature. As a base, we can still be found regularly in our cozy beach apartment in Noordwijk aan Zee. This apartment is located on the 3rd floor of a 5-floor building and has completely been renovated in 2019.

Because the balcony is quite large, with a sea view, and is conveniently located on the sun (south/west), you can enjoy everything that happens on the beach and in the sea all day long.

Due to the large parking lot at the rear of the apartment complex, you will have no problems finding a parking space and you will eventually only have to cross the boulevard to walk to the beach. There are several beach clubs situated that provide sunbed rental and nice food /drinks, so that you will be completely pampered.

The center of Noordwijk aan Zee with its many shops and restaurants is also about a 10-minute walk from the apartment.

Our main goal is to let you feel comfortable in our apartment and hope you have a wonderfull stay in Noordwijk aan Zee!

neighborhood_overview: Considering you're in Amsterdam, the neighborhood is quiet. Almost no cars pass the street. host_about:
I live in Amsterdam for half my life, stuck around after studying. Can't think of a better place to live! While staying at my place, I'll either show you around, or you'll just ignore my tips and advise and explore the city by yourself. I love music, going out, eating and travelling, so I can show you the restaurants in town, great clubs to go out, nice pubs to chill and drink a beer, venues to go to for a great concert or help you out with the do's (bike around) and don'ts (fall of your bike) for a tourist in Amsterdam

Feel welcome here! Don't be polite: ask my help or advise whenever you feel you can use it. And first of all, enjoy! I'd be happy to host you!

Cheers!

neighborhood_overview: Dappermarkt is one of the country’s oldest - and best - outdoor markets. It forms the multicultural heart of the neighbourhood along with such major arteries as Javastraat, which once only provided every manner of global grocery but is now beginning to feature more upscale cafes and terraces. One of the city’s largest general hospitals, OLVG, is also located here. Two stellar city parks, Oosterpark and Flevopark, provide quick escape from the relatively busy streets. Besides many cheap ethnic eateries and supermarkets, the area is attracting much more higher-end cafes and restaurants who are often re-inventing many of the area’s industrial monuments. On sunny days, the parks and terraces are filled with nice people.

However 7 years ago we found this little piece of paradise right at the Amsterdam forest. The house has had many cultural purposes in the past but was recently converted into this beautiful family home keeping the original details in place. Perfectly equipped for a family or potentially 2 couples. Central location, easy parking, busstop in front, bikes!
neighborhood_overview: What a unique location, the house is in Amstelveen and the garden is in Amsterdam. On the edge of the Amsterdamse Bos you can enjoy the beautiful greenery and at the same time the cosiness of the city at 10 minutes by bike. If you want to completely relax, close your doors and feel like you are miles from the city, but if you want to go shopping or go to a cafe, you take the bike or bus and you are in the bustle within 15 minutes! Supermarkets 5 minutes away, playgrounds, forest, goat farm, pancake restaurants, everything is nearby!
host_about: My name is Melissa & together with my boyfriend Nick and my 4 year old son Julius, I live in our dreamhouse right at the Amsterdam forest. It is our home and not a rental without a face & character, so we prefer people who can appreciate that and treat it with the respect it deserves. Feel free to ask me anything that is unclear or if your situation needs some flexibility, im easy to reach!

name: DESIGNER LOFT CITY CENTRE AMSTERDAM
description: Want that luxury feeling of staying in a designer loft? You can stay in our  bright and very big loft in our newly renovated 19th century schoolhouse! Quiet and private, but also at the canals and all the treats Amsterdam has to offer (Rijksmuseum, Van Gogh Museum, Anne Frank, beautiful parks, cute restaurants and coffee bars)! Our loft is 200 m2: 2 bedrooms with 2 personbed, 1 toddler baby bedroom,  bathroom and giant living room with entresol. We have a big balcony and a very big rooftop!
neighborhood_overview: We love our neighbourhood: old west of Asmterdam. You should go to the renovated tramremisse: the Hallen. You can have food from across the world, and sit inside or outside. Take something from 'Big Fish', we love their food. You can also go to the movies: the Filmhallen. Go out to Waterkant, an bar 5 minutes away in an parkinggarage with exotic food. We love the parks. Westerpark and Vondelpark. Go for a stroll. Or, little further away: take the free ferry to Amsterdam Nord, visit Eye; the museum, beautifull bar and movietheater. Go eat (make reservation) at Cafe Mordern: our favorite fancy dinnerplace.

name: Spacious 2-floor apartment - centre
description: Spacious and stylish apartment in A'dam centre. 10 min walk from Central Station but none of the noise and nuisance of the main tourist areas. The apartment has a warm atmosphere and is also well furnished for cozy nights inside or doing some work.
neighborhood_overview:
The 'Eastern Islands' is a part of Amsterdam Centre that is still a hidden gem. It is a 5 minute bike ride to all the main tourist areas but it is mainly occupied by Amsterdam residents.
-My house is just around the corner from the Maritime Museum, Artis Royal Zoo, The Tropenmuseum and Waterloo Square.
-The area itself can be divided into three parts:
-The Plantage Buurt with lovely stately lanes and greenery (I always feel like I'm on holiday there).
-The Eastern-Docks part which is in development and has some alternative edges with nice bars, galleries and multiple use spaces for festivals
-The Indonesian Neighbourhood is an exciting multicultural neighbourhood where you'll can get a (yummy) taste of all influences of Amsterdam.
host_about: I'm a 34 year old Dutch guy living in Amsterdam centre. I work in sustainable energy and international development. I've been lucky enough to travel all over the world so I know the importance of having a good 'base' to relax and re-energize in a foreign city. I enjoy giving tailored tips about where to go in Amsterdam, I'm usually quite up to date on the latest restaurants, bars etc. Amsterdam is a free city and I welcome you to come as you are.

name: Bright & Stylish Duplex with Rooftop in De Pijp
description:
Our home is located in trendy De Pijp, only a few minutes away from Centrum, museums and major attractions. It is on the 3rd and 4th floors of a classic Amsterdam building and features a 40-sqm rooftop terrace with matchless 360-degree views of the city. Supermarkets and trams are just a few steps away and the vibrant neighborhood is full of restaurants, cafes and boutiques.

As per Amsterdam rules, we are only allowed to host 4 guests max (children & baby incl.) - 7-night booking min. in summer
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is ideally located in the heart of De Pijp, currently one of Amsterdam's hippest neighborhoods. It is only 15 min away by foot from Museumkwartier and a very short bike/tram/metro ride from the city center and the main attractions.
In De Pijp you'll find the famous Albert Cuyp market ---the largest market in Amsterdam, and the Heineken Brewery. Plus plenty of great restaurants for all budgets, cafes, bars, trendy boutiques and concept stores. We'll be happy to share our favorite addresses and a neighborhood guide with you!
For grocery shopping, there are two supermarkets (Albert Heijn and Aldi) just two minutes away by foot, and a bakery around the corner.

name: Great Spot by Museum Square!
description: This beautiful and stylish apartment is located in the beautiful South of Amsterdam, in walking distance to our most famous museums! Perfect for a couple or someone exploring the streets of Amsterdam alone!
neighborhood_overview: Welcome to the Amsterdam area called 'Oud Zuid'. Literally translated 'Old South'. This neighborhood has been build around 1900 with the purpose of housing the rich. The streets are wide and dotted with large trees and the houses and apartments all have lots of character. Still today Oud Zuid is a residential area and therefore peaceful and friendly. On walking distance from my apartment you'll find loads of restaurants. Right on the corner of the street you'll find Affourtit which is open 7 days a week for diner. Good food for a fair price. Mostly French kitchen with some Dutch influences. If you walk a little further, to a street called Amstelveenseweg, you'll find anything from Japanese, Chinese, Indonesian, Thai, Italian, Indian, Vietnamese... Holland is quiet famous for it's Indonesian kitchen and restaurant Blauw is definitely the best in town. Keep in mind you won't stand a chance without reservations. If you're looking for haute cuisine you should definitely try Ron's Gastrobar

neighborhood_overview:
Our house is situated in a quiet residential area in Amsterdam-North. There are not many tourists here, but with the (free) ferry you are in downtown Amsterdam within 20 minutes. An excellent place to escape the crowdy parts to make the most of your stay.

Practical information:
* There is a supermarket at walking distance. It is called Plus and you’ll find it at the end of the street. It’s open till 8 P.M. More supermarkets and food shops you’ll find at the mall called Banne Buiksloot or Molenwijk, which is a 20 minutes’ walk. For the best bread & fresh croissants you can go to a nice bakery called BROOD which is located near the NDSM ferry. There is also a weekly market on the Van Der Pekstraat (wed, fri & sat). Here you can buy cheap, fresh products. For the market take bus 35 till central station, bus stop Mosplein.

Things to do and see:
In Amsterdam-North:
* You are close to the NDSM wharf, where you will find a couple of restaurants and bars

name: Comfortabel schip Amsterdam
description:
Near the city center of Amsterdam, our comfortably authentic sailing ship is located. On the one hand you will see the bustling city and on the other hand you will see the rural area of Amsterdam Waterland, Durgerdam.
The ship is modern, contemporary and equipped with every comfort. The ship feels like a wonderfully spacious ship with a sustainable jacket. Thanks to the renovation that has been carried out in a sustainable way, you can enjoy all the comforts with peace of mind in summer and winter.
host_about:
In 2012 gooide ik het roer om. Na 15 jaar in loondienst en vijf jaar wonen en leven op het water.
Door mijn voorliefde voor alles rondom recreatie en watersport heb ik in dat jaar de stap genomen mijn droom werkelijkheid te laten worden en mijn eigen zeilcharterbedrijf Amsterdam-Sailing te starten.

Met mijn bedrijf wil ik mij richten op de kwaliteit van het leven, mensen een plezierige tijd en unieke ervaringen te laten beleven, vakmanschap en natuurlijk de zeilvaart.

Onze missie is om van ons schip een voorbeeld te maken in de zeilchartervaart op het gebied van duurzaamheid. Zo denken we bij de verbouwing van ons schip zoveel mogelijk in groene oplossingen, worden CO2-vriendelijke materialen gebruikt en nemen we energie- en waterbesparende maatregelingen.

name: Cozy stylish space for a couple with free parking
description:
Newly renovated, modern and stylish space with a free private parking and the garden view.
The studio is situated downstairs of our home. Near the Zuidas, VU university, Olympic stadium and Amsterdam forrest. Public transportation tram/bus/metro is within 2min. walk.

neighborhood_overview:
Zuidas is a high-end international knowledge and business centre that is also one of the most important office locations in the Netherlands.
The Amsterdam forrest (Amsterdamse Bos) is three times the size of New York’s Central Park And entirely man-made. Spanning an impressive 1,000 hectares, the Amsterdamse Bos is among the largest city parks of Europe.
The Olympic stadium, the Olympic games of 1928 were held here and still hosting numerous sportive/cultural events.
VU (Vrije Universiteit) and VU academic hospital are one of the most well known university and hospital of the country.
Two large high-end indoor shopping malls are within 10min by bus.
host_about:
I was born and raised in South Korea and I spent last 25 years in several European countries. so I had a great opportunity to live in two completely different parts of the world. 

Since I got married with my Dutch husband and got two children I don’t travel as frequently as I used to do but I enjoy meeting new friendly people and visiting new destinations any time I can. 

Thanks to my background I speak Korean, Italian, English and Dutch fluently and I understand many other languages so the language barrier won’t be an issue in both as a hostess and as a guest. 
Looking very much forward to meeting you all!

name: Lovely apartment city center
description: Welcome to my lovely apartment in Amsterdam. It is perfectly located in the city center, yet in a relatively quiet residential area. Many city centre attractions are close by, with a large choice and variety of food and drinks hospitality just around the corner. The apartment has everything for a comfortable stay to experience the city. It has a big open plan living and kitchen area, with fantastic windows and light, with a view over one of the nicest canals in Amsterdam.
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is located in the city center, but in a relatively quiet residential area. This is a part of the city center that is not flood by tourists, and has a good mix of all kinds of people (families with children, students, elderly).
All city center attractions are close by to visit (Rijksmuseum and Van Gogh Museum are 25 minutes walk for example). The Nieuwmarket is just around the corner, with many nice bars (where many local people come as well, special tip is Café Fonteyn). On Saturday there is a nice biological market. Here is also the Zeedijk (in Chinatown), for great food (Birds, both the restaurant and the snackbar are famous for its Thai food). From the apartment you can walk to the famous Negen Straatjes in 15 minutes, for many shops and sightseeing along the old canals. The Marineterrein is ten minutes walk, a very nice place to hang out (Pension Homeland is really nice for a drink or sth to eat alongside the water) and even possible to take a swim there!

name: Comfortabel schip Amsterdam City
description: In the center of Amsterdam, our comfortably authentic sailing ship is located. The ship is modern, contemporary and equipped with every comfort. The ship feels like a wonderfully spacious ship with a sustainable jacket. host_about:
In 2012 gooide ik het roer om. Na 15 jaar in loondienst en vijf jaar wonen en leven op het water.
Door mijn voorliefde voor alles rondom recreatie en watersport heb ik in dat jaar de stap genomen mijn droom werkelijkheid te laten worden en mijn eigen zeilcharterbedrijf Amsterdam-Sailing te starten.

Met mijn bedrijf wil ik mij richten op de kwaliteit van het leven, mensen een plezierige tijd en unieke ervaringen te laten beleven, vakmanschap en natuurlijk de zeilvaart.

Onze missie is om van ons schip een voorbeeld te maken in de zeilchartervaart op het gebied van duurzaamheid. Zo denken we bij de verbouwing van ons schip zoveel mogelijk in groene oplossingen, worden CO2-vriendelijke materialen gebruikt en nemen we energie- en waterbesparende maatregelingen.

Tiny House is ideal as a hideaway for contemplatives, as a base for gourmets and culture lovers and as a nest for lovers.

This apartment is situated in a beautiful surrounding and close to all the exciting parts of Amsterdam.
Like the famous Rembrandtplein in the corner, the Zoo a few streets away.
The central station on walking distance.
The “Waterlooplein”, restaurants, museums, bars, clubs, pubs & coffee shops nearby and the canals next to you.
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is located in the city center of Amsterdam. It only takes 5 minutes by foot to arrive to the Waterloopsquare , the Red light district , the famous Rembrandtsquare and the Central station.
At the Waterloopsquare you find the nearest supermarkets, shops, coffeeshops and restaurants. Also in the direct area of the house you can find some nice bars and restaurants.

Tiny House is located in a place where history has literally and figuratively left its mark. It is on the route to the IJ (pronounced 'eye'), the estuary where ships from all over the world brought their treasures. On the quay is the cradle of capitalism and the insurance industry, with which the risks of each trip were covered and the often astronomical profits were distributed.

As a family business we run the quest house with passion and enthusiasm. 
Our goal is to provide our guests with warm and homely accommodation and let it be a home away from home.

name: Suburban parkside apartment
description: Welcome to your urban haven! This modern 2-bedroom apartment has charm and elegance. neighborhood_overview:
- Take a 15 minute walk through the leafy Vondelpark to museum square where the Rijksmuseum or Van Gogh museums await
- Grab a drink at our favourite local cafe Gent aan het Schinkel
- Jump on a bike (you can hire them nearby) and head into the quaint Amsterdam canals for some retail therapy. Our favourite for this is the 9 streets (~9 minute ride)
- Grab some dinner and a drink at the Foodhallen
- If you have kids there are lots of playgrounds within walking distance. The two largest are the JJ Cremerplein or by the Groot Melkhuis in the Vondelpark

neighborhood_overview: The Amsterdam Canal District is a neighbourhood in Amsterdam, Netherlands. The seventeenth-century canals of Amsterdam, located in the center of Amsterdam, were added to the UNESCO World Heritage List in August 2010. The Amsterdam Canal District consists of the area around the city’s four main canals: Singel, Herengracht, Keizersgracht, and Prinsengracht. From Brouwersgracht, the canals are generally parallel with one another, in a semi-horseshoe shape, leading gradually southeast into the Amstel river.

name: Amazing houseboat in Amsterdam city center
description:
Please note: Amsterdam implemented a 30 night restriction so our calendar may look very restricted. Feel free to find us online to discuss. Regards, Maarten Plesman and Laurien Meuter.

Our houseboat is right on the canal in the best possible location. You’ll love the ambiance of being on a houseboat and our 'Jordaan' neighbourhood with great restaurants and boutique shops.

There's a famous farmer's market on Saturday at Noordermarkt right outside your cosy home!
neighborhood_overview: Our neighbourhood, the famous Noordermarkt, is one of the best spots in Amsterdam. There is a market square in front of the houseboat with a well known organic food/farmers market on Saturdays and Vintage/Antiques market on Mondays. It provides a local buzz without being annoying and you feel privileged to have the easy access right from your doorstep. All other days, children play on the playground and restaurants put up their terraces there. It's really an Amsterdam experience to its fullest extent and it's mostly locals frequenting it. Close by are restaurants like Toscanini, Domenica, Joe&the Juice, Libertine, the famous Tweede Egelantiersdwarsstraat, and several nighttime hotspots.
host_about:
Hi there, we are Laurien  and Maarten. We love traveling and have done so extensively. We also enjoy being a host to you in one of the most exciting cities in Europe: Amsterdam. Our houseboat is in one of the best locations in Amsterdam and it has a special vibe to it, homely and cosy with a sense of excitement of being on the water whilst in the middle of the city. neighborhood_overview:
The Veemkade neighborhood in Amsterdam is a vibrant and dynamic area located along the waterfront. Known for its historical significance and modern charm, Veemkade offers a unique blend of old-world charm and contemporary urban living.

The neighborhood is characterized by picturesque canals, historic warehouses, and bustling streets lined with cafes, restaurants, and boutique shops. Residents and visitors alike are drawn to the area's lively atmosphere, cultural attractions, and stunning waterfront views.

Veemkade is home to a diverse community, with a mix of young professionals, families, and creatives. The neighborhood is known for its artistic flair, with galleries, studios, and performance spaces scattered throughout the area.

neighborhood_overview:
Watergraafsmeer, inside the ring, and the greenest neighbourhood in Amsterdam is easily reachable from the centre. Either walk along the Amstel river, take the tram or rent a bike. This area has been very up and coming over the last 10 years and we are really lucky to have so many excellent restaurants close by, whether it be Italian, Korean, Peruvian, or Mexican etc. The famous restaurant 'de Kas' where they grow their own veggies is just across the road in Frankendael park.
The great thing about this area of Amsterdam is that it is a very peaceful neighbourhood, has wide streets full of trees, lots of water and several parks and yet there all the amenities you could wish for when it comes to shops or sports facilities. There is even an open air swimming pool just 2km's away through the Flevopark.
We have lived here for over 20 years and still love this area of Amsterdam so much.

description: My boyfriend, our baby and I live in our beautiful palace in Amsterdam Old-West. We enjoy our modern apartment immensely. We have a large kitchen, with a bar and a big dining table. neighborhood_overview: If you walk out of the house and turn immediately to the left, you will end up on Jan Pieter Heijestraat. This is a street where you will find all kinds of nice stores, both for shopping and for buying good food and drinks. You can also enjoy a nice dinner, for example go to 'Café Lennep' on the waterfront, drink a beer at 'Gebrouwen door Vrouwen' or eat Thai food at the 'Golden Brown Bar'. If you go to the right on the Jan Pieter Heijestraat, from our street, and you walk it out, you arrive at the Overtoom (name of the street). Cross the street and you arrive at the Vondelpark. This is the largest city park in Amsterdam. You can walk around the park in about 50 minutes. It is also a great place to go for a run.
host_about: Hi, my name is Vivian. I live with my (very nice) boyfriend in our new apartment in Amsterdam Old-West. We are very proud of our place and are therefore very careful with all our stuff. name: Stunning canal view place
description: Welcome to my gem in Amsterdam’s beloved Jordaan district. This is a super authentic and cozy bedroom apartment offers an enchanting location and a lot of attention to detail that captures the essence of this historic city. While you stay at my place I will make sure you have all my top insider recs for exploring this amazing neighbourhood and beyond
neighborhood_overview:
The Jordaan is a historic neighborhood in Amsterdam, known for its picturesque canals, charming streets, and cultural significance. It's located in the city center, just to the west of the central train station. The neighborhood is characterized by its narrow houses with gabled facades, many of which date back to the 17th century. It has been given unesco status in 2010

Jordaan has a rich history and was originally a working-class area. Today, it's a trendy and desirable place to live, with a vibrant community and a mix of boutiques, cafes, art galleries, and restaurants. It's also famous for its weekly markets, like the Noordermarkt, and its proximity to the Anne Frank House.

The neighborhood has a relaxed, bohemian atmosphere and is a great place to explore on foot or by bike. It's a cultural hub with many art studios and music venues, making it a beloved area for artists and musicians.

neighborhood_overview:
Westerpark is a vibrant neighborhood located in the western part of Amsterdam, the capital city of the Netherlands. It is known for its mix of residential areas, cultural attractions, and recreational spaces, making it a popular place to live and visit.

One of the prominent features of Westerpark is the park after which the neighborhood is named.

The park is also home to several cultural establishments, such as the Westergasfabriek, a former gasworks turned cultural complex that hosts art exhibitions, festivals, markets, and concerts throughout the year.

Westerpark is also known for its vibrant social scene. The area is dotted with trendy cafes, restaurants, and bars, offering a wide range of culinary experiences.

neighborhood_overview:
This building apartment is located in one of the most pleasant areas of Amsterdam, the Pijp. With its colourful mix of cuisines, terraces and convivial cafés. From the beautiful landscaped gardens of Sarphatipark to the famous Albert Cuypmarkt street market, the Pijp oozes beatnik flair from every angle, and is has been a popular haunt for creatives, students and bohemian spirits since the 60s.

The Pijp is is located directly south of Amsterdam's city centre and it is part of the borough Amsterdam-Zuid, in a part of the city known as the Old South (Oud Zuid). It is served by the Pijp metro station. Most streets in the Pijp are named after Dutch painters, like Jan Steen, Frans Hals, Ruysdael and Vincent van Gogh. Diamantbuurt, Nieuwe Pijp and Oude Pijp are the three districts composing the area.

The busiest street market of the Netherlands, the Albert Cuyp Market, is located in De Pijp. It is open six days per week and attracts tourists. The former Heineken brewer

neighborhood_overview:
The Jordaan is possibly Amsterdam's most famous and romantic neighborhood. Formerly a typical working-class neighborhood with a colorful past, now extremely popular with visitors and residents due to the picturesque canals and the small narrow streets and alleys. Many artists live and work in the Jordaan. You will find many galleries, small shops, restaurants and cafes.
The Jordaan is the perfect neighborhood for a scenic city walk in the heart of Amsterdam. Look around you and enjoy the canal houses, the bridges and the canals full of boats .

Our house is situated in a quiet residential area in Amsterdam-North. There are not many tourists here, but with the (free) ferry you are in downtown Amsterdam within 20 minutes. An excellent place to escape the crowdy parts to make the most of your stay.

Practical information:
* There is a supermarket at walking distance. It is called Plus and you’ll find it at the end of the street. It’s open till 9 P.M. More supermarkets and food shops you’ll find at the mall called Banne Buiksloot or Molenwijk, which is a 20 minutes’ walk. For the best bread & fresh croissants you can go to a nice bakery called BROOD which is located near the NDSM ferry. There is also a weekly market on the Van Der Pekstraat (wed, fri & sat). Here you can buy cheap, fresh products. For the market take bus 35 till central station, bus stop Mosplein.

In Amsterdam-North:
* You are close to the NDSM wharf, where you will find a couple of restaurants and bars

name: Volledig duurzaam authentiek schip Amsterdam
description: On the enchanting island of NDSM lies Bracksand, a more than 120-year-old two-masted sailing clipper. Despite his age, Brackand is modern, contemporary and fully equipped. Bracksand feels like a wonderfully spacious large ship with a durable jacket. Thanks to the renovation that has been carried out in a sustainable way, you can turn on the underfloor heating with peace of mind and enjoy the fresh ventilation that blows through the cabins.
neighborhood_overview:
"All you need is already there." And that doesn't apply to all of us. You don't have to go far to see beauty! Because even if the ship stays in its beautiful place, there is so much to do. Once you step off the ship, you'll fall into the heart of the iconic and centrally located NDSM grounds. It's awkward, crowded, and cinematic. Bracksand is located on the "Green Cape", a part of the NDSM where you can record the rawness and history of the harbor area with all your senses. In the 1950s, NDSM was one of the world's largest and forefront recruiters! And this history can still be seen everywhere.

The four immense docks on the island can accommodate countless studios and nesting towns. For example, NDSM is a place for many artists, summer events and cozy festivals. Continuous companies such as MTV, Greenpeace are also located on this pure piece of Amsterdam. The Veronica boat is also there this summer, with open-air movie nights.

With the children, you can eat panc
host_about:
In 2012 gooide ik het roer om. Na 15 jaar in loondienst en vijf jaar wonen en leven op het water.
Door mijn voorliefde voor alles rondom recreatie en watersport heb ik in dat jaar de stap genomen mijn droom werkelijkheid te laten worden en mijn eigen zeilcharterbedrijf Amsterdam-Sailing te starten.

Met mijn bedrijf wil ik mij richten op de kwaliteit van het leven, mensen een plezierige tijd en unieke ervaringen te laten beleven, vakmanschap en natuurlijk de zeilvaart.

Onze missie is om van ons schip een voorbeeld te maken in de zeilchartervaart op het gebied van duurzaamheid. Zo denken we bij de verbouwing van ons schip zoveel mogelijk in groene oplossingen, worden CO2-vriendelijke materialen gebruikt en nemen we energie- en waterbesparende maatregelingen.

name: Relaxing Well located Apt - Amsterdam
description: Welcome to my lovely apartment. This beautiful, light and comfortable space is conveniently located in Amsterdam city. A  perfect place for couples or people on business trips. Literally across the street from RAI convention center and financial WTC, it is also surrounded by plenty of great  restaurants, cozy brunch cafes, and the best ice cream shop of Amsterdam. Next door you can find the green and relaxing Beatrix Park.  Just rent a bike next door and enjoy the full Amsterdam experience.
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is situated in the picturesque Rivierenbuurt neighbourhood of Amsterdam. The neighbourhood is situated in Amsterdam-Zuid, bordered by the river Amstel to the east, the Boerenwetering canal in the west, the Amstelkanaal in the north and the A10 motorway in the south.

The neighbourhood features many fine examples of Amsterdam School-architecture. The Dutch word Rivierenbuurt translates as 'Rivers Neighbourhood', which refers to the fact that most streets in the area are named after rivers in the Netherlands.

The apartment is literally across the street from the RAI convention center, very close to the train station and the metro 52, which takes you to the busiest centre of Amsterdam, literally in 7 minutes.
The apartment is also situated across the street from the finest restaurants and bars (best fish restaurant in town!).
host_about:
I’m passionate and curious by nature. I really enjoy meeting and hosting new people at my place. 
love traveling, living in different places and experiencing new cultures... that’s why Amsterdam is the city to be in.
As hobbies, apart from traveling I love diving, cooking (with nice music on), reading  books, do some (amateur) oil painting or just  going for long walks and picnics in Beatrix park (just next to my house) ...
Also like decoration and making my house  nice and cozy.
With friends we often indulge in a grilled meat or fish meal in restaurants nearby accompanied by a cold bottle of white wine. 
For travel or for work, come and try the true Amsterdam life,  I have a bunch of good tips for you :) Have fun!

My house is situated in the picturesque  Rivierenbuurt neighbourhood of Amsterdam city. The neighbourhood is bordered by the river Amstel. 
The neighbourhood features many fine examples of Amsterdam School-architecture. The Dutch word Rivierenbuurt translates as 'Rivers Neighbourhood', refers to the fact that most streets in the area are named after rivers in the Netherlands.

Until World War II the area had a sizable Jewish population which included Anne Frank and her family, who lived at Merwedeplein square until they went into hiding in the secret annex located in the Jordan.

Two minutes walking around my house you can be served by tram routes that takes you everywhere  in the city, such 4 and 12, bus routes 62 and 65, as well as Amsterdam metro and the train from Schiphol Airport, Amstel Station and Zuid Station. But if you want to try the real Amsterdam life you can always rent a bike just next door.


I’m sure you will have an amazing time !

host_about:
HI let me introduce to you my sweet family, Hester, Ibrahim and our son Khalil.

We are both creative directors, Hester in Amsterdam and Ibrahim in M'hamid el Ghizlane - Morocco " the door to the Sahara". We met 10 years ago while Hester was working with the women in the community. This incredible meeting resulted in a very happy, energetic and spirited boy who is now 8 years old.

Hester:

“I love to create wonderful experiences, concepts and brands where people take center stage.  I enjoy to share my international expertise and experience, and co-create social and economic improvement for local communities wherever possible.”

After her study at the Utrecht academy of arts, Hester worked as an international designer in New York, Istanbul and Mumbai. In 2004 she co-founded Butterfly Works, and as its art director was responsible for the development and monitoring of various concepts, products and brands.

In M'hamid Hester and Ibrahim developed the project "carpet of life" (Website hidden by Airbnb) a wonderful way to cherish your memories in a handmade carpet by the women in the oasis.

Ibrahim:

Ibrahim is co- founder and creative director of the Taragalte festival and fouder of the bivouac "Le petit prince" which is also the location of the festival. Taragalte festival is a yearly festival held in  M'hamid El Ghizlane the "door of the Sahara" on the border of Morocco and Algeria. This cultural event, based on cultural exchange is a tribute to the great Caravan to preserve our ancestral  heritage.

Ibrahim is from a nomadic Saharian background originally from M'hamid el Ghizlane the last oasis in the Draa valley. Since 20 years he is experienced and supports sustainable toursim in the region with the main focus on:

1. Preservation of the fragile Sahara environment
2. Development of  cultural exchange
3. Support of local talent
4. Sustainable tourism
5. Taragalte festival

Stay where all Amsterdam people want to live. Small private room in a historic canal house. In the vicinity of many museums, the Rembrandsplein and yet wonderfully quiet. Room with shower and toilet ensuite.

This room is part of a licensed guesthouse.
neighborhood_overview:
Quiet neighborhood - and we're sure our guests love that too!

The Rembrand Square, the Jewish Historical Museum, the Amsterdam Museum, the Rijkmuseum, the Van Gogh and the Urban Museum are within walking distance.
The opera and the Carre Theater are around the corner. There are many restaurants on Utrechtsestraat. Nearby food options.

De Pijp neighborhood starts 15 minutes on foot from us.
host_about: Since the summer of 2023, I have been managing Guesthouse Keizersgracht after succeeding Hans. Our team is dedicated to ensuring a pleasant stay in the heart of the Amsterdam Canal Belt. With six individually designed rooms, we offer a unique experience. We also work as part of the global German Seafarer's Mission in the port of Amsterdam, providing support to Seafarers. It would be my pleasure to welcome you to Guesthouse Keizersgracht.

description: This spacious and light apartment has everything you need for a great stay in Amsterdam. It has an amazing roof terrace and a fully equipped kitchen. It is easy accesible and located beautifully on the waterside, very close to the Vondelpark. Enjoy!
neighborhood_overview:
Oud Zuid is central: on one end you have Amsterdam’s nightlife and culture square Leidseplein and on the other Amstelveenseweg that is developing into a true culinary boulevard. And throughout the neighbourhood, a new bar seems to pop up every week. But for residents, firm favourites remain Vondelpark’s Vondelpark3 and Blauwe Theehuis. The Vondelpark remains Amsterdam’s most densely populated place-to-be whenever the sun shines. Besides this it’s nice to live near one of the greatest overviews of Western Art in the world. Two of the main museums, the Rijksmuseum and the Stedelijk Museum. For big shopping streets you can go to the PC Hooftstraat, Jacob Obrechtstraat, Cornelis Schuytstraat and Beethovenstraat.

Dam square: 4 km
Central station: 5 km
Museum square: 2,5 km
host_about:
We are Marten and Cindy from Amsterdam, love to sport, travel, discover other cultures and enjoy festivals once a while. Besides being a photographer, I (Cindy) love to paint, mainly caused by travelling. Marten works as a lawyer in Haarlem and is a creative writer in his spare time. 
In 2013 we experienced travelling and hosting with airbnb for the first time. We think it is very special; people open their house and make you feel at home. As a guest you respect and love this too? Then you can have such a beautiful experience. Because we like to meet other people and be of good service, this is a nice combination. 
We have a special interest in Spanish-language, same as the Spanish spoken countries, that for I (Cindy) worked as a volunteer and travelled for half a year in Latin-America.

p.s. Most of the time you will talk to me, but Dinah or Noehl is taking care of our apartment in Amsterdam, while I am gone!

neighborhood_overview:
The Romantic Panorama Suite is located in the southern tip of North Amsterdam, opposite Central Station. 1 km from the palace on the Dam, and 1, 7km from the Anne Frank House. Amsterdam North has an industrial feel and became one of the coolest neighbourhoods over the last years. More and more hotspots are popping up! Visit urban beaches like Café de Ceuvel and Pllek! Both perfect spots to relax and enjoy the warm weather on the waterfront. Other nice places overlooking the IJ-lake are film museum EYE (enjoy the sunset on their beautiful terrace!), seafood restaurant Stork and THT restaurant. One of our favourite areas in Amsterdam North is the NDSM Wharf. Known as one of the best festival locations of Amsterdam. North is also the place to be for vintage and thrift shopping. You can’t miss the monthly flea market in the IJ-hallen, a true second hand heaven.

Amsterdam Noord is upcoming and hip, with the Tolhuistuin, Eye Film Museum, and countless new hotspots such as the Caf
host_about: Ilco van der Linde (Haarlem, 7 december 1963) is de initiatiefnemer en organisator van diverse nationale en internationale campagnes en bewegingen voor verschillende maatschappelijke doelen. Without looking, come across the nicest pubs and restaurants.

neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is located in one of the nicest neighborhoods of Amsterdam: the pipe! The street itself is nice and quiet, but within walking distance you will find the famous Albert Cuyp market (350 m), where you can also find countless nice bars and restaurants.

Also our favorite bar- and shopping street The Utrechtsestraat is around the corner (450 m), where you will not only find all the nice bars and boutiques, but also the historic canals start so characteristic of Amsterdam. Here you will also find the royal theatre Carré and the Hermitage.

Around the corner is a hotel where you can rent bicycles. The perfect way to discover Amsterdam!

At the Amstel (400 m) there is a rental for boats, so that you can explore the canals like a real Amsterdammer.

For more tips, do not hesitate to message us!

name: Home with garden in Amsterdam | sleeps 4
description: Welcome to families & couples. Enjoy Amsterdam in the Summer. It’s the best time to visit the canals, the parks, the museums, the festivals. Stay in our 110m2 home with two kingsize beds and make yourself comfortable. Relax in the garden, enjoy the WiFi sound system, or get creative in the kitchen. There's FREE PARKING in front of the house. The tram is a 1-minute walk and brings you directly to Dam square,  Leidse square, the canals, Vondelpark etc.
neighborhood_overview:
Nieuw Sloten is a safe neighbourhood with lots of green. It was built under architecture to make the Olympics come to Amsterdam. Tramline 2 brings you straight into town and was voted one of the world’s most beautiful tram routes by National Geographic Travel.

A windmill museum, a cheese farm and a local beer brewery, as well as the church where Rembrandt’s granddaughter got married are within walking distance. Just like the picturesque village of Oud Sloten and a small national park with protected bird life.

When the sun drops, you can visit the nearby hotspots: A new rooftop restaurant and an underground club. Both are on 5-minute distance by tram.

More restaurants, a shopping centre, grocery shops and free playgrounds are all close by.
host_about: Hello, my name is Roos—a conceptual writer. I've lived in Paris and Ibiza, and traveled the world to finally come back to my hometown Amsterdam, where I feel settled at the moment. Trotting the globe, I've slept in noisy bunk beds to five star hotel rooms. In summer, we love travelling in our camper van, which brings us new family adventures.

name: nice clean sunny and central room
description:
The room is 15m² big and very bright with lots of sunlight. The apartment is on the top level in a nice and very quiet and green area next to the Westerpark, situated on a small canal.
You've got a double bed which you can share with 2 people. (Let me know if you wish to have two separate blankets.) There is a height adjustable table (sitting till standing height) and a spare monitor which you are welcome to use!
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is situated in the 'Spaarndammerbuurt', a neighborhood just outside the city center with nice bars and cafés and a wonderful park.
At night it is nice and quiet and you are in the centre in just 3 minutes, everything from here is walkable.

For example you can walk to the Jordan neighborhood (nice bars and restaurants, canals, old canal houses, galleries) or the Westerpark (jogging, hanging by the pool, nice cafés and bars).

If you are walking to the center don't miss out on the 'Haarlemmerstraat' which is a cool and hip street with lots of cafés and small unique shops.

There is a great open water swimming spot very close by as well, also really nice to sit there on the peer, let me know and I will give you the details!

name: Canalhouse in the Center
description:
This beautiful canal house is a charming place conveniently located in the heart of Amsterdam’s Canal District near 'Het IJ'. The estuary where during the Golden Age, merchandise and spices were supplied and stored from all corners of the world.

The canal house is situated within walking distance of the main museums, popular shopping areas, and historic landmarks.

The house is just renovated and geüpgraded in January 2024.
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is located in the city center of Amsterdam. It only takes 5 minutes by foot to arrive to the Waterloopsquare.
It’s 15 minutes walking to the Red light district and the famous Rembrandtsquare. 20 minutes walking to the Central station.
At the Waterloopsquare and Rembrandtplein you find the nearest supermarkets, shops, pubs, coffeeshops and restaurants.
Also in the direct area of the house you can find some nice bars and restaurants.

The nearby Foeliestraat reminds us of the latter, a spice that has been loved since the Middle Ages and is better known as nutmeg. Walk with us through the area.

In the 19th century, the neighborhood was a refuge for Jews who had fled the pogroms in Eastern Europe. They had already been preceded by Sephardic Jews who had been expelled from Spain and Portugal since 1492. The Portuguese synagogue is still a reminder of them, which for a long time was considered the largest synagogue in the world.

neighborhood_overview: The house is situated in Amsterdam Noord. An industrial, vibrant and upcoming part of Amsterdam. You can find local pubs, many new restaurants dotting the waterfront, the cultural hotspot and quickly transforming NDSM-wharf with an urban beach at the river IJ, the EYE-museum, ADAM tower and some nice hidden spots (eg. cafe de Ceuvel). In opposite direction a 15 minute bike ride along the historic Buiksloterdijk takes you to the pastoral quiet of old farmland situated in "polders" (land reclaimed from the sea). It is a landscape that could have been painted by Jacob van Ruisdael. During summer you can swim in natural waters nearby the house.

neighborhood_overview:
The neighborhood is called Spaarndammerbuurt. A lovely area that used to be working class but has developed a lot over the past decade. It features some great architecture from the beginning of the 20th century of the famous 'Amsterdamse School'. You can also find shops, bars and restaurants on the mean street at a 5 minute walk. Like pretty much all of Amsterdam, the area is very safe and quiet both during the day and night.

neighborhood_overview:
Staying in the Jordaan and experiencing the Amsterdam canals around the Noordermarkt is an absolute joy. The Jordaan is a charming and historic neighborhood, filled with narrow streets and quaint houses. The neighborhood has a lively atmosphere and is home to many boutiques, cafes, and restaurants. It's a great place to take a walk and explore, whether you're looking for some quiet time or want to experience the hustle and bustle of the city.

The Noordermarkt is a lively market square located in the heart of the Jordaan. On Saturdays, the square transforms into a bustling market where locals and visitors can enjoy a variety of food and drinks, browse unique products and crafts, and take in the energy of the city. It's a great place to stop for a quick bite, do some shopping, or simply relax and people-watch.

description:
Feel welcome in our monumental house, which is light and spacious, and it has exceptional views of the city.
Our house is really in the middle of the Jordaan with all the facilities that this beautiful city offers. Restaurants, friendly little stores, good supermarkets, everything is within walking distance: you will be part of this beautiful part of Amsterdam!

neighborhood_overview:
The Jordaan neighbourhood is tucked inside central Amsterdam and quite conveniently located. Arguably Amsterdam's most famous district, the area contains an upscale assortment of art galleries, patio restaurants, cafes and street musicians.
Trendy Jordaan's narrow canals and streets are flanked by indie boutiques, cosy pubs, and hip eateries. Stalls at the Noordermarkt square market offer jewellery, clothes, antiques and organic food. Antiques Centre Amsterdam sells vintage ceramics and paintings, while smaller galleries in the area focus on innovative contemporary art. Other attractions include the Houseboat Museum and the Anne Frank Huse!

neighborhood_overview:
Our apartment is located on "centrumeiland" which is the newest part of Ijburg Amsterdam.
Ijburg is a beautiful neighbourhood at the edge of Amsterdam. Being right at the water of the IJmeer lake makes it a special get away from the touristy centre. Life on Ijburg is a little slower, very modern and connected to nature.

A land of wind and water, IJburg is Amsterdam's newest neighbourhood, made up of four man-made islands, with even more in development. Located in the easternmost part of the city, this up-and-coming area has quickly become popular among those who love modern architecture and water sports. Locals frequent the charming neighbourhood cafes and higher-end bars clustering around the yacht haven, whilst windsurfers, swimmers and beach goers head straight to Strand Blijburg for the spectacular sunsets and windswept views.

However it's important to note that our part of Ijburg is still under construction and you do get quite a bit of a building side

neighborhood_overview:

neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is located between Westerpark and Jordaan

Westerpark is not just a park, but a lively neighborhood that beautifully blends nature, culture, and entertainment. The park itself is a wonderful place to relax, picnic, or even catch an outdoor movie in the summer.

The neighborhood is home to a variety of restaurants, cafes, and trendy boutiques. It's also known for the Westergasfabriek, a former gasworks factory that's now a cultural venue hosting a range of events from music festivals to food markets.

Jordaan is a picturesque and lively district known for its beautiful canals, narrow streets, and quaint houses. Once a working-class area, Jordaan has transformed into one of Amsterdam's most desirable and trendy neighborhoods.

The area is brimming with cozy cafes, unique boutiques, and art studios.
It's also home to the famous Anne Frank House and a host of other historic sites. The weekly Noordermarkt flea market is a must-visi

neighborhood_overview:
The small, hidden district called Kadoelen where we live is in a quiet area of the city. It's a hidden gem within Amsterdam's city ring and outside the crowded touristy areas, yet only 3 minutes from the highway and 20 minutes from the city center by bike, public transport or car. Our streets have lots of green, and hardly any traffic. Next door to our home is the largest green meadow within the city limits, full of birds. We have a private parking space and friendly neighbors all around.

Amsterdam Noord (North) is the upcoming area of the city and full of old and new attractions.

The Neighborhood
The neighborhood is peaceful, cosy and quiet, away from the busy city center hustle but very close by. It is close to numerous attractions.

It is walking distance to the lovely Vondelpark (an ideal summer hangout spot), Museumplein (museum district with the famous Rijksmuseum, Van Gogh museum and Stedelijk Museum) and PC Hooftstraat (luxury shopping street). Also the Olympic stadium and Zuidas business district are around the corner.

The streets around the apartment offer everything you need: a lot of nice cafes and restaurants, a bookshop, bike rental, supermarket, pharmacy and Saturday market.

With public transportation it is only 10 minutes to the city center/canal area (Leidseplein, 9 straatjes, Spui etc.).

name: Deluxe Modern Amstel Canal View
description:
A deluxe and modern renovated 1st floor apartment with fascinating River view, 1 Master Bedroom, Rain Shower, app.: 861 ft.²

2 French balconies in front (Amstel River View) and 1 in the back.

It's like a Presidential Suite with a spectacular view!
neighborhood_overview:
The location
The apartment is situated in one of the best locations of Amsterdam City center and has breath-taking wide views of Amsterdam's most famous and prestigious “canal” – the Amstel River - that gives Amsterdam its name.

The apartment is located on the first floor of the building, allowing spectacular views from the living room. This location places the property right in the heart of Amsterdam’s Unesco World Heritage site, yet meters away from “the Pijp”, a neighborhood famous for it’s bars, cafes and restaurants, as well as the city’s biggest market.

The apartment is situated right in between the glamorous Royal Theater – “Carré” – and the exclusive “Amstel hotel”. A little further along is the romantic “Magere Brug” (Skinny Bridge), the “Hermitage Museum” and the Opera house (“Het Muziektheater”).

You can wake up in the morning and take in the views with a cup of coffee on one of the balconies, before popping into a neighborhood bakery
